canonical:
  title: 王處順充鹽城鎭使
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒奉處分大藩鎭之爲制也中屯銳師外列諸戍用備腹心之患固憑牙爪之勤前件官深蘊壯圖挺生勇氣姜維若在未占稚兒焦度相逢應饒健物每展報恩之節累申伐叛之功眷彼塩城居于海岸苟或一同失理實爲四遠多虞遂徵處順之名俾守防姧之任爾其効勇夫之重閉致危俗之安居蹔固封壃無念及瓜之限但逢寇孽勉敭破竹之聲事須補充塩城鎭使
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 王處順充鹽城鎭使
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 牒奉處分。大藩鎭之爲制也。中屯銳師。外列諸戍。用備腹心之患。固憑牙爪之勤。前件官。深蘊壯圖。挺生勇氣。姜維若在。未占稚兒。焦度相逢。應饒健物。每展報恩之節。累申伐叛之功。眷彼塩城。居于海岸。苟或一同失理。實爲四遠多虞。遂徵處順之名。俾守防姧之任。爾其効勇夫之重閉。致危俗之安居。蹔固封壃。無念及瓜之限。但逢寇孽。勉敭破竹之聲。事須補充塩城鎭使。
korean:
  title: 왕처순 충 염성진사
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: 처분을 받들어 통첩한다. 큰 번진(藩鎭)은 그 제도는 안에는 정예한 군사로 둔(屯)을 치고, 밖에는 여러 위수병을 벌여 놓는데, 내부[腹心]의 근심을 막으려면, 진실로 용맹한 무장을 얻어야 할 것이다. 전건의 왕처순은 깊이 장한 꾀를 쌓아두었고, 뛰어난 용기를 가졌다. 강유(姜維)가 만약 있더라도 어린아이로 취급할 수 없고, 초도(焦度)와 서로 만났으면, 응당 건장한 인물이라고 할 것이다 그는 매양 보은(報恩)의 절개를 펴서, 여러번 반도(叛徒)를 친 공을 이루었다. 저 염성(鹽城)을 보니, 해안에 있어서 정말 그 한 고을이 다스려지지 못하면 실로 사방의 걱정이 많을 것이다. 그러므로 결국 처순을 불러서 간악한 적을 막는 책임을 지게 하노니, 그대는 용부(勇夫)의 무거운 태도를 본받아 위태로운 풍속을 편안하게 할 것이다. 봉강(封壃)을 견고히 하기 위해서 만기(滿期)를 생각하지 말 것이요, 오직 도적을 만나면 여지없이 격파하는 데 힘을 다할 것이다. 마땅히 그를 염성진사에 충당한다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1090_010_0220&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Appointment of Wang Cheo-soon as Commander of the Salt City Garrison
  author: Choi Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: 'By official dispatch, this appointment is hereby made. Such is the design of a great garrison fortress: within, elite troops are stationed in strong positions; without, various outposts are arrayed in defense. To prevent dangers from within the realm, one must truly secure valiant commanders. This Wang Cheo-soon has accumulated profound strategic wisdom and possesses exceptional courage. Should even the legendary Jiang Wei himself appear, he could not be deemed his inferior; meeting the renowed Jiao Du, he would surely be recognized as a man of superior mettle. He has repeatedly displayed the virtue of gratitude and achieved many triumphs in subduing rebels. Consider the Salt City, situated upon the coastal reaches—should its governance falter even once, calamity and anxiety would surely spread to the four corners. Therefore, we summon Cheo-soon to bear the grave responsibility of defending against treachery and deceit. Let him emulate the steadfast resolve of brave warriors and bring peace to an imperiled land. Strengthen the frontier and do not heed the passage of time; when bandits appear, spare no effort in crushing them utterly. Thus Wang Cheo-soon is hereby appointed Commander of the Salt City Garrison.'
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Jiang Wei (姜維, 202-264) was a celebrated general of Shu during the Three Kingdoms period, known for his military prowess and strategic brilliance.
  - key: ''
    value: Jiao Du (焦度) was a distinguished general from antiquity, referenced here as an exemplar of martial excellence.
  - key: ''
    value: The phrase 'do not heed the passage of time' refers to serving without concern for term limits or tenure, implying unwavering commitment to the post.
